    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1836_08_30_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"/><choice><orig>Edgeworthtown</orig><reg>Edgeworthstown</reg></choice>
                        <date when="1836-08-30">Aug<hi rend="superscript">t.</hi> <unclear>30<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi></unclear> 1836</date></dateline>
                    <salute>
                        Dear Sir
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    Have you written yet to
                    M[superscript]rs[/superscript]. Carmichael?
                    If you have not I wish you
                    would not delay longer to
                    do so - for it is most cruel
                    to keep her in suspense.
                    You promised M[superscript]r[/superscript]. and
                    M[superscript]rs[/superscript]. Lockhart that you would
                    write directly -
                    If you have written give
                    me the satisfaction of a line
                    to tell me so - &amp; direct under
                    cover to T[superscript]s[/superscript] Drummond Esq
                    Dublin Castle -
                    Yours truly
                    Maria Edgeworth
                    M[superscript]rs[/superscript]. Carmichaels address is
                    S[superscript]t[/superscript]. Helens Jersey
                </p>
                <p>
                    <!--More body paragraphs as needed.--></p>
                <p>
                    <!--More body paragraphs as needed.-->
                    <!--Where there's a page break record it inside the relevant body paragraph like this, 
                  with the self-closing page-break element. n="2" indicates the START of the second page.-->
